<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-B0vP5xmATw1+K9KRQjQERJvTumQW0nPEzvF6L/Z6nronJ3oUOFUFpCjEUQouq2+l" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <!-- <script src="//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.0/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
    <script src="//code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.1.min.js"></script> -->
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title></title>
    <style media="screen">
        input{
            border:1px solid transparent;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #000000;
            position: relative;
            top: -9px;
            pointer-events: none;
            margin-top: 4px;
        }

        .sr{
            display:flex;
        }
        .header{
            background-color:#b0661b;
            width: 100%;
            border-bottom: 8px solid black;
            border-top: 8px solid black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
    <div class="p-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">

                <div class="row">
                    <div class="text-center header"><h2 style="">Generals Terms & Conditions</h2></div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>1.	NAME AND LOCATION OF THE PROJECT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The name of the project shall be <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> comprising residential plots and commercial units planned to be available in <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;">.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>2. Booking:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>Plots are offered on ownership basis to general public having Pakistan nationality and companies based in Pakistan, and the plots shall be booked on first come first served basis.
                        The application form, terms and conditions, and schedule of payment etc. will form an integral part of this contract and will be binding on both the parties. Acceptance of booking form is subject to approval of the company. The company may accept or reject any application form without assigning any reason. The allotted plot is liable to be cancelled at any stage in case of submission of forged documents or if the information given in application form is found to be false.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>3.	PRICE OF UNIT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The price of units is fixed and is offered on no escalation basis, provided the applicant/allottee pays his/her total dues/charges within the agreed period of payment schedule. The price includes development of all services as specified in the specification of development work, and shall neither be increased nor escalated except, if the applicant/allottee fails to pay his/her total dues/charges within the agreed period of payment schedule.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>4.	CONFIRMATION OF BOOKING:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The booking shall be confirmed through provisional allotment letter after receipt of 50% payment of unit price form the applicant.
                        Allocation/allotment of any unit in the project shall remain provisional and will be confirmed only after receiving full and final payment.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>5.	PAYMENT OF INSTALLMENTS:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>a.	The payment of instalment shall be strictly made by the applicant on due dates according to the schedule of payment. In case of failure, a first notice of 15 days shall be issued. If the applicant/allottee fails to make the payment within specified period of 15 days, a second notice will be issued to him/her extending the payment period 15 days more. If the applicant/allottee fails to pay within the extended period of 2nd notice, then a final notice shall be issued allowing him/her to settle his/her total over dues within 15 days time. If the applicant even does not comply with the final notice, then his/her allotment shall be cancelled under the intimation to the applicant/allottee and the amount paid by the applicant/allottee shall be refunded by the company as per terms of clause 7 of this agreement.<br><br>

                        b.	In case of default/overdues the allottee will also be liable to pay penalty charges @ 2% per month on total outstanding amount on aggregate basis and/or penalty rates as per company's prevailing policy with respect to it.<br><br>

                        c.	The company reserves the rights to accept/reject the payment made against pending cases and any partial payment against due/overdue instalment may be accepted/rejected at the sole discretion of the company, acceptance or rejection of installments is the sole discretion of the company.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>6.	TRANSFER OF BOOKING/ALLOTMENT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>a.	The allottee shall not sell, transfer, mortgage, lien and/or assigns the unit to any individual, bank or company, before giving prior written consent to the company and before obtaining clearance from the company.
                        <br><br>b.	Transfer of booking/allotment shall be governed by the company's prevailing transfer policy and shall be allowed after the payment of 50% of total cost of unit and will be subject to the clearance of all dues/charges at the time of receiving such application. Company reserves the right to accept/reject such transfer application at its sole discretion.
                        <br><br>c.	Company shall charge the requisite transfer fee as prescribed from time to time that initially defined at Rs. 25,000/- per plot.
                        <br><br>d.	Documentation as prescribed by the company with respect to transfer shall be required to complete by the transferor & transferee.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>7.	SURRENDER OF BOOKING/ALLOTMENT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>If an applicant subsequently decides to surrender the booking/allotment or fails to pay the installments on demand as per clause 5 above, he/she shall lose all his/her rights and entitlement of the allotment and the allotment shall stand cancelled under intimation to him/her and he/she will be allowed refund after deduction of 30% of the total sales price of the unit as service charges and refund in 18 months after the said unit has been re-booked by some other buyers and the new applicant pays in lump sum all the installment/charges due up-to-date as per payment schedule of old booking.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>8.	COMPLETION OF THE PROJECT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>a.	The company will complete the development work as per clause 20 of specification of development work and handover physical possession of the unit to the allottee with development completed in all respect however the completion of project will be subject to the timely payments by the allottees and also subject to the necessary cooperation required for the development of the project from govt authorities.
                        <br><br>b.	The company will fulfill its obligation of timely completion of the project subject to the fulfillment of the allottees commitment except if it is on account of force majeure as per clause 22 (C). Further in case of delay in the payment of instalments by the allottees, the company shall be at liberty to revise and make reasonable changes in the time schedule and shall also have the discretion to escalate the prices minimum 1% per month of the total value of the unit. Such charges, demanded by the company, shall be paid by the allottee.
                        <br><br>c.	The price of the unit may be escalated due to unexpected increase in the cost of raw material utilized for development, labor charges and/or forces majeure and/or if the applicant/allottee fails to pay his/her total dues/charges within the agreed period of payment schedule.
                        <br><br>d.	In case of unit, the size/area is increased at the time of final demarcation/construction or at the time of possession, then the cost difference due to such increase in size/area shall be paid by the allottee as and when demanded by the company at prevailing rates. In case of decrease of unit size/area the company is liable to refund the difference at the purchase price paid by the allottee.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>9.	TAKING OVER POSSESSION:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>a.	The allottee shall take over possession of the unit within 3 months of completion of payment to the company.
                        <br><br>   b.	After proper handing over of the unit to the allottee. The allottee shall be responsible for safety of the unit. The company shall be responsible to rectify all defects if any within 3 months time from the date of possession.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>10. ABANDONMENT OF THE PROJECT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>If, for any reason, the project is abandoned, the company will refund the total amount received from the allottee after 6 months of announcement and also subject to the surrender of all original receipts, documents, etc. to the company. The allottee shall have no claim for interest/profit or damages of any nature whatsoever from the company.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>11. ARBITRATION:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p> All disputes between the company and the applicant/allottees relating to the allotment shall be referred to the arbitrator as nominated by the management board of the company, and the decision of the arbitrator shall be final and binding on both the parties.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>12. PAYMENTS:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>All payments shall be made by the applicant/allottee strictly as per agreed payment schedule through pay order/bank draft/Cash in favor of developer's account directly in the designated branches of company's authorized bank, or in shape of cash directly to the company's office, or through company's authorized marketing agents. </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>13. PAYMENT OF TAXES:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The allottee shall pay all taxes levied by the federal/provincial/district government/local municipal bodies, etc. these taxes will include those existing at present and which shall be levied by the above mentioned and/or other authorities in future.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>14. EXCLUSION FROM THE OCCUPANCY VALUE OF THE UNIT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The occupancy value of the unit, as mentioned in the schedule of payment, includes the price of land, cost of development/construction as specified in the specification. The occupancy value of the unit does not include the cost of stamps, registration fee, documentation charges and other expense in connection with the execution of lease deed etc., similarly the allottee will pay to the company the costs of stamps, registration fee, documentation charges and other expenses in connection with the execution of sale deed.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>15. MEMBERSHIP OF THE FORT MUNRO RESORTS COMMUNITY:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>Before the transfer and/or taking possession of the unit by allottee, the allottee shall become the member of the <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> community which will be formed to look after the common and general services of the housing scheme. Allottee shall pay the membership fee and the annual dues/charges of the <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> community along with the expense for the common services that is maintenance and upkeep of the road, water supply etc., the allottee shall agree to abide by the rules and regulation of the
                        <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> community. The allottee shall further agree to abide by any addition, alteration to these rules and regulation which may be made by the member of the <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> community. No allottee will be allowed to self-transfer mortgaged or sub-lease his/her unit till such time the dues of the <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> community have been cleared, similarity, no unit built on the land of the project shall be sold, transferred, sub-lease, mortgaged and/or given on hire till such the dues of the <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> community have been cleared and with the prior permission/consent of the <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> community.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>16. AVAILABILITY OF THE SERVICES:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The company will develop the area, build roads and provide water, sewerage services and electricity sub-station as specified in the clause 20. Although the company would make every effort to obtain permanent domestic electric connection, the availability of the above-mentioned services is dependent on the authorities and the company accept no responsibility if the availability of these services are delayed</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>17. PROGRESS OF WORK:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The company shall maintain steady progress of the work subject to the timely payments by the allottees and subject to the necessary cooperation required for development of the project from govt. authorities. However, the company will fulfill its obligation of timely completion of the development of the scheme subject to the fulfillment of the allottees commitment.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>18. DEVELOPMENT TO CONFIRM TO THE PLANS AND SPECIFICATIONS:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The unit shall be developed strictly according to the approved layout plans and specification. However, if the situation arises when some changes proposed by Local/Govt. authorities in our Master Layout Plan, then company shall also be bound to incorporate such changes in our Master Plan, for which the allottee shall extend full cooperation and such changes will be binding on all the allottees.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>19. ADDRESS FOR CORRESPONDENCE AND NOTICES:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>Notice(s) of payment and all other notices and correspondence shall be sent at the last given address of the applicant, as per record of the company. The company shall, however, not be responsible for non-delivery of notices, correspondence etc.; due to change of address, the communication whereof has not been made to the company.</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>20. SPECIFICATION OF DEVELOPMENT WORK:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>The development and construction would be done according to the plan/specification; however, minor changes may be made if necessary.
                        a.	Road and Walkways:
                        b.	Bituminous carpeted roads with camber in the middle.
                        c.	Water Drainage & Sewerage System:
                        d.	Water Supply:
                        e.	Electricity Supply: The Company's responsibility is limited to provide installation of transformer, laying of cables.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>21.	SCHEDULE OF PAYMENT:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>Schedule of payment is annexed with this Terms & Conditions and should be considered as integral part of this agreement</p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>22.	OTHER MISCELLANEOUS:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>a.	The rights of the Common Services/Facility area will be retained by the company and the allottee/occupants will have no share, claim, rights over it. The use of exterior walls, roof top and other common areas are reserved by the company for any commercial or for any other purpose, involving monetary gain. In such case, allottee of units, individually and collectively do not have any claim as profit, share in benefits, etc. in any shape, whatever, it may be.
                        <br><br>  b.	That it expressly understood by the allottee/applicant that no claim for damages or otherwise will be made on or against company, if the company interrupts the development/construction work or is unable to keep the time schedules due to force majeure, war, natural calamities, mishaps, civil commotions, strikes, terrorism, law & order conditions, any departmental and/or individual adverse action, changes in policies of the Government and/or any valid and tangible reason.
                        <br><br> c.	The allottee shall not bring inside the Unit or the Project goods or machinery which are hazardous and combustible/flammable and shall not use the unit for any purpose other than for which it was constructed and allotted.
                        <br><br> d.	After taking over of possession of the unit, allottee will not be allowed to fix any water tank/reservoir, geyser, grill in balcony/terrace, as the beauty of the project will be affected adversely. If required, the same will be designed by the company and fixed in proper manner at allottee cost.
                        <br><br> e.	The allottee shall not carry out any additions or alterations involving structure of the building (the structure includes columns, slabs, and beams) nor shall change the original elevation of the building or any part thereof under any circumstances. The restriction will remain enforce even after taking over possession of the unit.
                        <br><br> f.	The allottee shall keep clear the common ways, passages, staircases and street etc. for all the allottee/buyers/occupants of the project.
                        <br><br> g.	The allottee shall not misuse the common areas, not he/she shall cover/encroach the open area on the ground floor, or anywhere in the project.
                        <br><br>  h.	The company will form the management for the project maintenance services. The services include security guards, janitorial staff, maintenance staff, gardeners, care takers, plumbers and electricians. The service charges for these services shall be applicable for all units booked/purchased.
                        <br><br>  i.	Apart from above facilities provided by the management entity; one year advance will be paid by the allottee on demand, as the management entity shall be responsible for the maintenance of the project commencing from the date of handing over the possession of first unit in the project. If any allottee delays in taking possession of unit because of his/her own reason, he/she will clear immediately on demand all the accumulated maintenance charges, from the date intimated by the company in its letter till the date of possession. The company reserves the rights of cancellation in case taking over of possession is delayed beyond six months.
                        <br><br> j.	Allottee shall have to take "permission to build" and clear the related payments before starting any construction work at the unit after getting the permission to build on his or her unit or clearance of all dues of his/her unit, the allottee has to start construction within one year and complete strictly as per the drawing/elevation, design/approve by the company. With the company consent and <input type="text" name="" value="" style="width:150px;"> approval the allottee shall not allow the construction work. The construction will be carried out according to plan specification however minor changes in the designed may be made, if considered necessary by the company.
                        <br><br>  k.	All units number and/or other identification numbers given in the layout plans, booking and/or allocation letters pertaining to allotment are on adhoc, temporary and tentative basis and the company reserves the rights to amend/change or renumber the same if found necessary
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>23.	THE APPLICANT AGREED:</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>a.	To permit the representative of the company/management entity to enter the unit for ascertaining the observance of all the covenants or for all laying, testing or repairing, services, cables, pipes, drains and other items etc. the applicant shall take all the precautions against tempering/fouling of all other services.
                        b.	Not to make partition, alteration, addition and holes, attachments or adhesion of any nature without the prior written consent of the company.
                        c.	To pay monthly utility charges to the management entity for the upkeep the project. I/We further agree that, if in case of non-payment/failure in timely payment my/our utility services may be disconnected on my/our own risk and cost.
                        d.	To use the residential units for residential purpose only, as specified and approved by the company.
                        e.	Not to use the residential unit for any unlawful activity.
                        f.	Company will not accept any changes/cutting/over writing in these agreement and every one must have to follow these Terms and Condition.
                    </p> </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 sr"><h4>24.	DECLARATION::</h4> </div>
                    <div class="col-md-12 sr"><p>I/We have read and understood all the terms & conditions and I/We hereby agree to abide by them unconditionally, I/We further undertake that the company reserves the right to change, and or delete any conditions and rules and regulations at its discretion with or without assigning any reason or notice thereof and the allottee/applicant shall accept the decision of the company in this regard.</p> </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
